column5: Saw the same thing today,what a couple /three weeks?. Looks like this weekend cold again for a bit. Let's hope it does not drag on to long .
I see a toon fish, in the very near future.
Wind must have been blowing out. Last night the bay was open. It was too dark to see how far though.
Johnstons beach either way open this morning.
No ice to be seen from the bottom of the bay and we had a east wind this morning. That might be it.
Ya at 6 am this morning the N/E winds, had the waves crashing the shore line.
Yes, it is funny how ugly it can look with a east wind.
